---
layout: default
title: GitLab.com
suppress_header: true
extra_css:
  - gitlab-com.css
extra_js:
  - gitlab-com.js
---
.wrapper
  .image-title
    .color-bg
      %div
        %h1 GitLab.com
        %h3 unlimited free repositories and collaborators
        .header
          %a#join-community.gs-button{href: "https://gitlab.com/users/sign_in"} Sign Up
        .header-feature.hidden-sm.hidden-xs
          %ul
            %li
              %i.fa.fa-check
              %p Free public & private repositories and unlimited collaborators.
            %li
              %i.fa.fa-check
              %p Runs GitLab Enterprise Edition with issue tracking, wikis, and CI.
            %li
              %i.fa.fa-check
              %p No installation required, sign up above for a free account!
        .header-feature-small.hidden-md.hidden-lg
          %ul
            %li
              %h4 Free public & private repositories and unlimited collaborators.
            %li
              %h4 Runs GitLab Enterprise Edition with issue tracking, wikis, and CI.
            %li
              %h4 No installation required, just sign up above for a free account!
  .sub-wrapper
    .container
      .row.advantages
        .col-xs-1.col-md-1
        .col-xs-12.col-md-5
          %h2
            Advantages
            %a{name: "advantages"}
          %ul
            %li Unlimited repositories
            %li Unlimited private collaborators
            %li 10GB disk space per project (including Git LFS)
            %li Unlimited total disk space
            %li Completely free, no credit card required
            %li
              %a{href: "/2016/04/19/gitlab-partners-with-digitalocean-to-make-continuous-integration-faster-safer-and-more-affordable/"} Unlimited CI Runners to do parallel testing
            %li
              %a{href: "/2016/02/18/gitlab-dot-com-now-supports-an-alternate-git-plus-ssh-port/"} Alternate SSH port for git+ssh (443)
          %p
            %a{href: "https://gitlab.com/explore"} Explore the public projects on GitLab.com
            (no account needed)
        .col-md-4.hidden-sm.hidden-xs
          = image_tag "/images/wordmark.png"
        .col-xs-6.col-md-1
      %hr.divider/
      .row.users
        .text-center.users
          %h2
            GitLab.com is used by more than 100,000 people,
            %br/
            including these organizations:
          %br/
        .logos
          .logo
            .logo_ibm
              = image_tag "/images/gitlab-com/ibm.png"
          .logo
            .logo_samsung
              = image_tag "/images/gitlab-com/samsung.png"
          .logo
            .logo_microsoft
              = image_tag "/images/gitlab-com/microsoft.png"
          .logo
            .logo_shopify
              = image_tag "/images/gitlab-com/shopify.png"
          .logo
            .logo_ibm
              = image_tag "/images/gitlab-com/toyota.png"
        %br/
        .disclaimer
          %small All logos and trademarks are the property of their respective owners.
      %hr.divider/
      .row.support
        .col-xs-6.col-md-1
        .col-xs-6.col-md-4.text-center
          %i.fa.fa-briefcase.hidden-xs.hidden-sm
        .col-md-1.hidden-sm.hidden-xs
        .col-xs-12.col-md-6
          %h2
            Support Package
            %a{name: "support-package"}
          %ul
            %li
              Free users can use the
              %a{href: "https://gitlab.com/gitlab-com/support-forum/issues"} GitLab.com Support Tracker
              if they have questions.
            %li
              Users can purchase Gitlab.com Bronze Support providing you with email support directly for timely, personal and private answers. The cost is $199.80 annually (for up to 20 users) for next-business-day response time.
      .row.panels
        %h2.text-center
          Select package
          %a{name: "select-package"}
        .row{ data: { equal: ".col-md-6" } }
          .col-md-6
            .gitlab-com-panel.panel.panel-default
              .panel-heading
                %h3.panel-title Free
              .panel-body
                %b Unlimited
                private and public repositories
                %br/
                %b Unlimited
                private collaborators
                %br/
                Support via
                %a{href: "https://gitlab.com/gitlab-com/support-forum/issues"} the forum
                .btns
                  %div
                    %b Free
                  %a.btn.btn-lg.btn-default{href: "https://gitlab.com/users/sign_up"} Sign up
          .col-md-6
            .gitlab-com-panel.panel.panel-purple
              .panel-heading
                %h3.panel-title Gitlab.com Bronze Support
              .panel-body
                %b Unlimited
                private and public repositories
                %br/
                %b Unlimited
                private collaborators
                %br/
                %b Next Business Day Support
                %br/
                %b Direct email access to support team for timely, personal and private answers
                .btns
                  %div
                    %b $199.80
                    (for up to 20 users)
                  %a.btn.btn-lg.btn-purple{href: "https://customers.gitlab.com/subscriptions/new?plan_id=2c92a0fe58068f08015807ef5f2f66df"} Order support
      %hr.divider/
      .row.security
        .col-xs-1.col-md-1
        .col-xs-12.col-md-6
          %h2
            Availability and Security
            %a{name: "availability-and-security"}
          %ul
            %li
              GitLab.com is monitored 24/7. For updates follow
              %a{href: "https://twitter.com/gitlabstatus"} @gitlabstatus
              or see our
              = succeed "." do
                %a{href: "https://status.gitlab.com/", title: "status"} status page
            %li
              Our servers are hosted on Amazon Web Services (AWS), Digital Ocean, and Azure, we use configuration management, and we patch our servers at least once a week. Our
              %a{href: "https://gitlab.com/gitlab-com/runbooks"} runbooks are public
              as is our
              %a{href: "https://gitlab.com/gitlab-com/infrastructure/issues"} operational issue tracker
              \.
            %li
              GitLab offers
              %a{href: "http://docs.gitlab.com/ce/profile/two_factor_authentication.html"} Two-Factor Authentication (2FA) via a mobile application or a U2F device,
              %a{href: "http://doc.gitlab.com/ce/security/rack_attack.html"} rate limiting,
              %a{href: "http://doc.gitlab.com/ee/administration/audit_events.html"} audit logs,
              and passwords are one-way encrypted.
            %li
              GitLab.com
              %strong
                cannot
              be integrated with your LDAP server, if you need this please
              = succeed "." do
                %a{href: "https://about.gitlab.com/features/"} host GitLab yourself
              or
              = succeed "." do
                %a{href: "https://about.gitlab.com/githost-io/"} use our GitHost.io service
        .hidden-xs.hidden-sm.col-md-4
          %i.fa.fa-terminal
        .col-xs-1.col-md-1
      %hr.divider/
      .row.support
        .col-xs-6.col-md-1
        .col-xs-6.col-md-4.text-center
          %i.fa.fa-wrench.hidden-xs.hidden-sm
        .col-md-1.hidden-sm.hidden-xs
        .col-xs-12.col-md-6
          %h2
            GitLab.com settings
          %a{name: "gitlab-com-settings"}
          %p
            For information like fingerprints of GitLab.com's SSH host keys and
            settings of GitLab Pages, CI, Runners, etc., see the separate
            = succeed "." do
              %a{href: "settings/"} GitLab.com settings page
      %hr.divider/
      .row.import
        .col-xs-1.col-md-1
        .col-xs-12.col-md-6
          %h2
            Plenty of import options
            %a{name: "import-options"}
          %p
            You can easily import your projects from GitHub, Bitbucket, Google
            Code, Fogbugz, any Git repository by URL, or import an exported
            GitLab project.
          %p
            %a{href: "http://doc.gitlab.com/ce/workflow/importing/README.html"} See our documentation
            for all your import options.
        .hidden-xs.hidden-sm.col-md-4
          = image_tag "/images/gitlab-com/import_options.png"
        .col-xs-1.col-md-1
      %hr.divider/
      .row.import
        .col-xs-1.col-md-1
        .col-xs-12.col-md-9
          %h2#why-gitlab-com-will-be-free-forever
            %a{name: "free-forever"}>
            Why GitLab.com will be free forever

          We want GitLab.com to become the most popular service for hosting
          projects. To achieve this goal, GitLab.com is free, both for public
          and private projects. Unlike other companies in this space, there is
          no limit to the number of collaborators. We think that in the future
          most repository hosting will be free in the same way email hosting is
          free today. So we thought, why wait? Let's make it free for everyone
          now. Our subscriptions for GitLab EE on-premises bring in more
          than enough revenue to pay for the hosting of GitLab.com.
          The revenues from EE and other Products are growing fast enough to keep up
          with the growth in GitLab.com usage.
          We see GitLab.com as a way to make GitLab more known and popular. In the future we might
          introduce paid features like projects sizes above 10GB and Windows/OSX CI Runners.
          We intend to keep the features that you have now free and monetize only new features.

          %h3
            = link_to('Sign Up', 'https://gitlab.com/users/sign_in', class: 'btn btn-purple')
